      • createActions

        protected javax.swing.Action [] createActions()
        Description copied from class: DialogWrapper
        Creates actions for dialog.

        By default "OK" and "Cancel" actions are returned. The "Help" action is automatically added if DialogWrapper.getHelpId() returns non-null value.

        Each action is represented by JButton created by DialogWrapper.createJButtonForAction(Action). These buttons are then placed into south panel of dialog.

        Overrides:
        createActions in class DialogWrapper
        Returns:
        dialog actions
        See Also:
        DialogWrapper.createSouthPanel(), DialogWrapper.createJButtonForAction(javax.swing.Action)
